<subSubSection id="C35F655AFFC8FFDCFF35FB6EB7519D07" pageId="3" pageNumber="441" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BFA36D1FFC8FFDCFF35FB6EB5179FF6" blockId="3.[151,738,1135,1198]" box="[151,307,1172,1198]" pageId="3" pageNumber="441">
(
<figureCitation id="137E2A54FFC8FFDCFF3DFB6EB5349FF6" box="[159,272,1172,1198]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1108,1132]" captionTargetBox="[161,1428,532,1079]" captionTargetId="figure-161@1.[151,1436,522,1088]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. a–d. A. anchoroides Lin &amp; Zhang sp. nov. e–h. A. drepanoides Lin &amp; Zhang sp. nov. a, c, e, g. dorsal view; b, f. lateral view; d, h. face." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5449847" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5449847/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="441">Figs 1e–h</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="137E2A54FFC8FFDCFEBEFB6EB50E9FF6" box="[284,298,1172,1198]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1588,1612]" captionTargetBox="[159,1428,190,1559]" captionTargetId="figure-19@5.[151,1436,179,1568]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. A. drepanoides Lin &amp; Zhang sp. nov. a. genital capsule; b. abdominal apodemes; c. connective; d. pygofer dorsal appendage; e. style, lateral view; f. style, ventral view; g. aedeagus, lateral view; h. aedeagus, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5449851" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5449851/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="441">3</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFA36D1FFC8FFDCFF35FB26B15B9E66" blockId="3.[151,1437,1244,1846]" pageId="3" pageNumber="441">
<emphasis id="B931EAC3FFC8FFDCFF35FB26B50D9FAE" bold="true" box="[151,297,1244,1270]" pageId="3" pageNumber="441">Description.</emphasis>
Crown, face except anteclypeus and anterior margin of pronotum yellow-whitish. Central and hind part of pronotum, scutellum and anteclypeus brown. Scutum light yellowish. Paired blurred spots at transition from vertex to face brown. Eyes grey, and basal triangles blackish. Fore wing and hind wing light brown, transparent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFA36D1FFC8FFDCFF35FAB2B6E59E3B" blockId="3.[151,1437,1244,1846]" box="[151,705,1352,1379]" pageId="3" pageNumber="441">
Abdominal apodemes narrow and short (
<figureCitation id="137E2A54FFC8FFDCFDC2FAB2B6909E3B" box="[608,692,1352,1379]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1588,1612]" captionTargetBox="[159,1428,190,1559]" captionTargetId="figure-19@5.[151,1436,179,1568]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. A. drepanoides Lin &amp; Zhang sp. nov. a. genital capsule; b. abdominal apodemes; c. connective; d. pygofer dorsal appendage; e. style, lateral view; f. style, ventral view; g. aedeagus, lateral view; h. aedeagus, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5449851" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5449851/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="441">Fig. 3b</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFA36D1FFC8FFDCFF65FA96B5E99D63" blockId="3.[151,1437,1244,1846]" pageId="3" pageNumber="441">
Pygofer side with 8 macrosetae at cephalo-ventral angle. Central part of subgenital plate with about 4 macrosetae in irregular row near lateral margin (
<figureCitation id="137E2A54FFC8FFDCFDFEFA6AB68A9EF2" box="[604,686,1424,1450]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1588,1612]" captionTargetBox="[159,1428,190,1559]" captionTargetId="figure-19@5.[151,1436,179,1568]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. A. drepanoides Lin &amp; Zhang sp. nov. a. genital capsule; b. abdominal apodemes; c. connective; d. pygofer dorsal appendage; e. style, lateral view; f. style, ventral view; g. aedeagus, lateral view; h. aedeagus, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5449851" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5449851/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="441">Fig. 3a</figureCitation>
). Apex of dorsal appendage not bifurcated, base broad, tapering to apex, moderately curved, resembling horn in lateral view (
<figureCitation id="137E2A54FFC8FFDCFC8DFA4EB7A09E97" box="[815,900,1460,1487]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1588,1612]" captionTargetBox="[159,1428,190,1559]" captionTargetId="figure-19@5.[151,1436,179,1568]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. A. drepanoides Lin &amp; Zhang sp. nov. a. genital capsule; b. abdominal apodemes; c. connective; d. pygofer dorsal appendage; e. style, lateral view; f. style, ventral view; g. aedeagus, lateral view; h. aedeagus, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5449851" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5449851/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="441">Fig. 3d</figureCitation>
). Area between style apical and subapical teeth convex, resembling a sickle in lateral view, with apical tooth much longer than subapical tooth (
<figureCitation id="137E2A54FFC8FFDCFB6FFA22B13B9EAA" box="[1229,1311,1496,1522]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1588,1612]" captionTargetBox="[159,1428,190,1559]" captionTargetId="figure-19@5.[151,1436,179,1568]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. A. drepanoides Lin &amp; Zhang sp. nov. a. genital capsule; b. abdominal apodemes; c. connective; d. pygofer dorsal appendage; e. style, lateral view; f. style, ventral view; g. aedeagus, lateral view; h. aedeagus, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5449851" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5449851/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="441">Fig. 3e</figureCitation>
). Aedeagal shaft with no apical or subapical processes, gonopore subapical, pre-atrial process surpassing aedeagal shaft and almost straight (
<figureCitation id="137E2A54FFC8FFDCFEEEF9DAB59B9D63" box="[332,447,1568,1595]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1588,1612]" captionTargetBox="[159,1428,190,1559]" captionTargetId="figure-19@5.[151,1436,179,1568]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. A. drepanoides Lin &amp; Zhang sp. nov. a. genital capsule; b. abdominal apodemes; c. connective; d. pygofer dorsal appendage; e. style, lateral view; f. style, ventral view; g. aedeagus, lateral view; h. aedeagus, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5449851" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5449851/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="441">
Figs 
<quantity id="4CBD9B34FFC8FFDCFE26F9DAB5869D62" box="[388,418,1568,1594]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="3.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="441" unit="g" value="3.0">3g</quantity>
, h
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFA36D1FFC8FFDCFF65F9BEB7519D07" blockId="3.[151,1437,1244,1846]" box="[199,885,1604,1631]" pageId="3" pageNumber="441">
<emphasis id="B931EAC3FFC8FFDCFF65F9BEB5579D06" bold="true" box="[199,371,1604,1630]" pageId="3" pageNumber="441">Measurement.</emphasis>
Length of male 2.7–2.9mm (including wing).
</paragraph>
